"ENIGMA has since expanded to examine 
alterations in brain structure and function across a number of disorders, with or without also 
including genetic data.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"The name ENIGMA, which Webster defines as “mysterious, 
puzzling, or difficult to understand or explain”, also invokes the endeavors of the British 
team at Bletchley Park to decode highly sophisticated war-time communications during 
World War II; similarly, ENIGMA brings investigators together to decode the complex and 
multifaceted factors that influence brain structure and function.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"At the time of its inception, 
the focus on candidate genes in imaging genetics led to a crisis of reproducibility, but less 
biased genome-wide association studies (GWAS) required tens or hundreds of thousands of 
participants to achieve significance.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"In 2014, ENIGMA was funded as an NIH Big Data to 
Knowledge (BD2K) Center of Excellence.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"ENIGMA has resulted in the largest-ever 
neuroimaging datasets of numerous disorders to date, including Major Depression, 
Schizophrenia, and Epilepsy.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"ENIGMA currently includes 30 disease working groups, 4 
groups on healthy variation over the lifespan, and 9 groups focused on methods 
development.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"There are currently over 1400 investigators from 40 countries participating in 
ENIGMA activities (see Figure 1).",nihms-1672220.pdf
"ENIGMA has received funding through over 20 grants 
across the United States, the European Union, and Australia.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"For a recent review of broader 
ENIGMA activities, see ( Thompson et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
2020 ).,nihms-1672220.pdf
"Formation of ENIGMA Brain Injury
In the fall of 2016, the ENIGMA Brain Injury group was formed.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"From its inception, it was 
clear that the complexity of brain injury would necessitate specialized groups that could 
more readily address unique features of the varying cohorts.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"Within the first year, multiple 
subgroups were identified, including Pediatric Moderate/Severe Traumatic Brain Injury 
(TBI) (msTBI) ( Dennis et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"2020 ), Military-Relevant TBI ( Tate et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"2020 ), and Sport-
Related Head Injury ( Koerte et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
2020 ).,nihms-1672220.pdf
"Soon after, groups for Adult msTBI ( Olsen et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"2020 ) and Acute Emergency Department (Civilian) Mild TBI were formed, followed by a 
group focusing on Intimate Partner Violence ( Esopenko et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
2020 ).,nihms-1672220.pdf
"The newest groups to 
be formed are focused on emerging imaging methods that may have particular relevance in 
TBI, namely Magnetic Resonance Spectroscopy (MRS)( Bartnik-Olson et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"2020 ), Arterial 
Spin Labeling (ASL), resting state fMRI (rsfMRI), and Cognitive Endpoints (see Figure 1).",nihms-1672220.pdf
"Additional groups will likely be added in the future to address other aspects of 
methodological and imaging development as well as other TBI-relevant patient populations.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"The focus of this special issue is on the ENIGMA-Brain Injury working group’s efforts to 
facilitate research in TBI and concussion.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"Goals and Benefits
The overarching goal of the ENIGMA effort is to create a collaborative framework where 
investigators can work together to address questions and objectives that require large 
amounts of data and to promote replication of preliminary findings through the use of 
multiple and independent samples.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"Collaboration enables investigators to overcome common 
obstacles which often limit sample sizes in this area of research, including the expense of 
acquiring neuroimaging data and limited sample sizes.",nihms-1672220.pdf
"The intent of ENIGMA is to 
accelerate the pace of investigation through harnessing the enormous intellectual resources Wilde et al.",nihms-1672220.pdf
